  "text": "This oscillation is caused by variations in the electrowetting force with the droplet position. Electrowetting is commonly characterized by the change in contact angle on a substrate as a function of applied voltage. In the basic model, the contact angles (θ) will depend on the voltage (V) between the pad and the droplet and the liquid wetting angle (θ 0 ) without the applied voltage. These can then be related to the thickness (δ) and dielectric strength (ε 0 ,ε R ) of the Cytop layer by the Young Lippman equation [CITATION_1] :",
